<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🚀 WD003 Week 8 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Final Polish — Publish Your Portfolio · <strong>Course:</strong> Portfolio Site · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This is the final week. You bring together <strong>every section</strong> from the past seven weeks, fix anything awkward, and <strong>publish</strong> your site so anyone can visit it. This is no longer practice — this is <em>your</em> work, going out into the world.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Publishing means putting your site at a real web address. You can use Replit's Webview share link or GitHub Pages. When you have a link, anyone can open it.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each situation below. Before you check your own site, write what you expect.</p>
<pre><code>A visitor opens your site on a phone for the first time.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Walk through what they see, from the Hero to the Footer. Does every section still look right on a small screen?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>A visitor clicks your dark mode button, then refreshes the page.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>If you added the localStorage bonus, what should happen? If you did not, what happens instead?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>A visitor fills in your contact form and clicks Send.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Describe, in order, what they should see. If any step is missing on your site, note it here so you can fix it.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛 (Final Checklist)</h2>
<p>Go through your own site and find what is broken or unfinished. For each item, write <strong>what is wrong</strong> and <strong>how you will fix it</strong>. A great submission is honest — finding your own bugs is the skill.</p>
<p><strong>Check A — Sections.</strong> Open your site and confirm all five are present and complete: Hero, About, Projects, Contact, Footer.</p>
<p><strong>What is missing or unfinished? How will you fix it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Check B — Design system.</strong> Are your colors, font, and spacing consistent across every section? Or does one section look like it came from a different site?</p>
<p><strong>Where is it inconsistent? How will you fix it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Check C — Features.</strong> Does the dark mode toggle work? Does the contact form show a thank-you message? Do the nav links scroll smoothly? Does the page hold up on mobile?</p>
<p><strong>Which feature is broken or rough? How will you fix it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Publish and Present 📸</h2>
<p>Finish, polish, and <strong>publish</strong> your site.</p>
<ol>
<li>Fix everything you found in the checklist above.</li>
<li>Make sure you have <strong>at least three</strong> project cards.</li>
<li>Walk through the whole site top to bottom and tidy the spacing, font sizes, and colors.</li>
<li><strong>Publish</strong> with Replit's Webview link or GitHub Pages, and open the public link to confirm it works.</li>
<li>Send the link to a friend or family member and ask what they think.</li>
</ol>
<p>When you finish, send your <strong>public link</strong> plus <strong>PC and mobile screenshots</strong>, then present your site in writing. Use these sentence starters — write 5 to 7 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The public link to my site is …</p>
<p>The five sections of my site are …</p>
<p>I set up my design system by …</p>
<p>My dark mode works by …</p>
<p>On mobile, my site changes by …</p>
<p>My favorite part is …</p>
<p>The hardest part of the whole project was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Final Presentation 🎥</h2>
<p>Now record your final presentation video on your phone (or a parent's phone). This is the big one — you are showing off eight weeks of work. Talk through it like you are presenting <em>your</em> site to an audience. Try to use these words: <strong>portfolio</strong>, <strong>design system</strong>, <strong>dark mode</strong>, <strong>responsive</strong>, <strong>published</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Open your published link and scroll through every section.</li>
<li>Explain what each section shows.</li>
<li>Toggle dark mode and show your site on a narrow screen.</li>
<li>Say what you are most proud of, and what was hardest.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your published link + PC and mobile screenshots + your final presentation video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
